The Premier League returns this weekend after European football in midweek. Table toppers Liverpool welcome Watford in the early kick off, seeking to extend their eight-point gap at the top of the table. Bournemouth travel to Chelsea, Burnley host Newcastle and Leicester City take on Norwich. The late kick off will see Southampton clash with West Ham United. Saturday, December 14
13:30 Liverpool vs Watford
16:00 Burnley vs Newcastle United
16:00 Chelsea vs AFC Bournemouth
16:00 Leicester City vs Norwich City
16:00 Sheffield United vs Aston Villa
